Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.37,0:00:04.82,Italics,Na,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}The Storm Dragon Veldora was \Nsealed by Unlimited Imprisonment.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.78,0:00:04.07,sign_27841_421_Unlimited_Impris,Text,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(608,1)}Unlimited Imprisonment
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.20,0:00:09.16,Italics,Na,0000,0000,0000,,To break that seal, Rimuru ate Veldora.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.80,0:00:11.96,Italics,Na,0000,0000,0000,,They both began the process \Nof analyzing the seal,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.96,0:00:14.83,Italics,Na,0000,0000,0000,,Veldora from the inside and \NRimuru from the outside,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.22,0:00:18.00,Italics,Na,0000,0000,0000,,with the goal of setting \NVeldora free someday.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.15,0:00:22.76,Italics,Na,0000,0000,0000,,After gaining several new \Nskills and leaving the cave,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.76,0:00:24.26,Italics,Na,0000,0000,0000,,Rimuru met the Goblins,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.87,0:00:29.12,Italics,Na,0000,0000,0000,,and he ended up vowing to protect \Nthem from an attack by Direwolves.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.19,0:00:46.07,Show_Title,Title,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1614,389)}That {\c&H471E13&}Time {\c&HCD9612&}I Got {\c&H471E13&}Reincarnated {\c&HCD9612&}as a {\c&H7E4F0A&}Slime
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.73,0:02:04.40,Ep_Title,Title,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1023,1)}Episode 3: Battle at the Goblin Village
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.69,0:02:13.28,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like I shouldn't expect to \Nfind many who can fight Direwolves.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.22,0:02:16.96,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,They all look too scrawny and beat-up.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.09,0:02:23.26,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Talk about pressure...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.34,0:02:26.80,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone, do you understand our situation?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.80,0:02:27.60,Main,Rigur,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.60,0:02:31.51,Main,Rigur,0000,0000,0000,,We are prepared for a life-or-death battle!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.64,0:02:35.17,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,No need to get all worked up. Just relax.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.17,0:02:38.31,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Think only about doing the best you can.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.37,0:02:41.64,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't mean to sound that cool...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.34,0:02:47.07,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,But first, take me to where the wounded are.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.12,0:02:55.33,Main,Elder,0000,0000,0000,,We did all we could for them, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.14,0:02:58.31,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,That's deeper than I'd imagined.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.31,0:03:01.07,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Did their claws and fangs \Ndo that much damage?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.07,0:03:03.08,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Well, might as well try it...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.73,0:03:07.11,Main,Elder,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What are you doing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.19,0:03:12.13,Main,Goblin,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? I'm...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.01,0:03:15.80,Main,Elder,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Your wounds...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.29,0:03:17.51,Main,Goblin,0000,0000,0000,,They're healed!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.50,0:03:20.18,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,I guess it never hurts to try!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.00,0:03:24.31,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,I never thought eating him and throwing \Nall those potions in my body at him
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.31,0:03:26.30,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,would be so effective!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.50,0:03:30.32,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,These healing potions really work!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.77,0:03:35.57,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Next! And next!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.57,0:03:38.18,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Since I ate all those hipokute \Nherbs, I've got plenty to spare!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.18,0:03:39.45,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,I'll heal 'em all!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.91,0:03:45.53,Main,Elder,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You are magnificent, Rimuru-sama!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.04,0:03:51.18,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,That's the last of the wounded.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.83,0:03:52.76,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Now, then...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.65,0:03:55.11,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,We'll build a fence.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.11,0:03:56.77,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Fortify the village's defenses!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.45,0:03:58.14,Main,Elder,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.02,0:04:07.02,sign_5827_43_Great_Forest_of_,Text,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(524,1)}Great Forest of Jura
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.17,0:04:10.01,Main,Boss,0000,0000,0000,,It's a fine night.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.80,0:04:14.17,Main,Boss,0000,0000,0000,,Veldora's protection has \Nvanished from this forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.17,0:04:16.28,Main,Boss,0000,0000,0000,,We have nothing to fear any longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.72,0:04:20.05,Main,Boss,0000,0000,0000,,Tonight, we will destroy the Goblin Village
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.05,0:04:23.19,Main,Boss,0000,0000,0000,,and create a foothold here \Nin the Great Forest of Jura!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.04,0:04:28.33,Main,Boss,0000,0000,0000,,We will rule this forest!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.20,0:04:34.45,Main,Boss,0000,0000,0000,,Our claws can tear apart any monster,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.45,0:04:37.74,Main,Boss,0000,0000,0000,,and our fangs can chew any monster to pieces!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.05,0:04:56.97,Main,Boss,0000,0000,0000,,Hah!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.97,0:05:00.28,Main,Boss,0000,0000,0000,,What good will such a flimsy fence do?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.05,0:05:02.96,Main,Ranga,0000,0000,0000,,Father...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.49,0:05:08.80,Main,Boss,0000,0000,0000,,A slime?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.65,0:05:12.17,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Turn back now, and we won't take any action.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.17,0:05:14.05,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Leave this place at once!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.22,0:05:19.04,Main,Boss,0000,0000,0000,,Insolence! No mere slime can \Norder around us Direwolves!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.04,0:05:20.90,Main,Boss,0000,0000,0000,,Trample down that fence!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.90,0:05:23.64,Main,Boss,0000,0000,0000,,Spill the blood of those lowly Goblins!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.20,0:05:40.16,Main,Boss,0000,0000,0000,,Threads?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.77,0:05:42.59,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,That's my skill, Steel Thread.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.62,0:05:42.95,Skill,Text,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(523,1)}— Steel Thread —
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.34,0:05:45.20,Main,Boss,0000,0000,0000,,This is your doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.20,0:05:46.21,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.21,0:05:48.73,Main,Boss,0000,0000,0000,,A puny monster like you dares do this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.73,0:05:50.38,Main,Boss,0000,0000,0000,,I will squash you!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.58,0:05:51.54,Main,Ranga,0000,0000,0000,,Father!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.09,0:06:01.35,Main,Elder,0000,0000,0000,,Rimuru-sama!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.35,0:06:07.69,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}That's Sticky Thread.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.35,0:06:08.81,Skill,Text,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(320,260)\fad(526,1)}— Sticky Thread —
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.15,0:06:10.67,Main,Boss,0000,0000,0000,,This won't hold me!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.44,0:06:15.76,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Skill: Water Blade!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.42,0:06:42.36,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Hear me, Direwolves!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.99,0:06:45.25,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Your boss is dead!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.25,0:06:49.10,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,I'll give you the choice: submit or die!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.37,0:06:54.76,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Yikes...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.76,0:06:59.41,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,What if they go the "We'd rather die than \Nsubmit" route and attack all at once?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.77,0:07:02.33,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,I wish they'd just turn tail and run...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.51,0:07:05.87,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! Predator!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.89,0:07:16.46,Italics_Top,Great Sage,0000,0000,0000,,Analysis complete.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.80,0:07:20.30,Italics_Top,Great Sage,0000,0000,0000,,Acquired ability to mimic Direwolf.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.88,0:07:20.09,sign_10499_82_Acquired_ability,Text,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(734,224)}Acquired ability to mimic Direwolf
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.30,0:07:25.64,Main,Great,0000,0000,0000,,Direwolf species skills Supreme Sense of Smell, \NThought Communication, and Menace acquired.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.26,0:07:25.64,sign_10580_86_Thought_Communic,Text,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(191,1)}Thought\NCommunication
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.43,0:07:25.64,sign_10584_87_Supreme_Sense_of,Text,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(187,1)}Supreme Sense\Nof Smell
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.43,0:07:25.64,sign_10584_88_Direwolf_Species,Text,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(730,1)}Direwolf Species Skills
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.59,0:07:25.64,sign_10588_85_Menage,Text,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(152,1)}Menace
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.56,0:07:27.46,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.02,0:07:32.64,Skill,Text,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(320,220)\fad(148,1)}— Mimic —
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.16,0:07:39.47,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Hear me! I will let you go just this once.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.91,0:07:44.41,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,If you refuse to yield to me, \NI will allow you to leave this place!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.82,0:07:48.29,Skill,Text,0000,0000,0000,,{\bord1}— Menace —
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.21,0:07:55.40,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, run away already!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.12,0:08:01.55,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,It's not working? They still want to fight?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.17,0:08:11.98,Main,Wolves,0000,0000,0000,,Our pack yields to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.54,0:08:13.15,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.57,0:08:15.75,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,They could have just run away...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.19,0:08:17.75,Main,Rigur,0000,0000,0000,,U-Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.75,0:08:20.03,Main,Elder,0000,0000,0000,,D-Did we win?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.02,0:08:23.24,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, looks that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.09,0:08:27.08,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,It's good that there's no \Nneed for fighting anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.08,0:08:29.55,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Yep, yep. Nothing beats peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.47,0:08:37.36,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,And so the battle at the Goblin \NVillage ended remarkably easily.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.36,0:08:39.89,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.22,0:08:47.88,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,What now?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.88,0:08:52.64,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Who's gonna look after not only the \NGoblins, but all these pups, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.35,0:08:57.49,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,I guess their numbers are \Nabout the same. Then...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.25,0:09:00.56,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, listen up!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.79,0:09:07.66,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,So, I'm going to have you all \Npair up and live together!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.00,0:09:09.91,Main,All,0000,0000,0000,,Pair... up?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.20,0:09:11.59,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Do you understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.28,0:09:16.19,Main,Elder,0000,0000,0000,,Rimuru-sama, what does "pair" mean, exactly?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.19,0:09:17.92,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,It means to form groups of two.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.71,0:09:19.51,Main,Goblin,0000,0000,0000,,Groups...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.51,0:09:20.75,Main,Wolf,0000,0000,0000,,...of two?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.85,0:09:24.77,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Good!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.77,0:09:26.89,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Yesterday's enemy is today's friend!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.89,0:09:31.09,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,You're all to work together and get \Nalong as friends from now on! Got it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.09,0:09:32.22,Main,All,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.22,0:09:35.18,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Help each other out, and make it work.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.08,0:09:39.10,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,That settles things for now...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.51,0:09:42.53,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,So, um...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.53,0:09:46.43,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,What's going to be important now \Nis food, shelter, and clothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.85,0:09:49.61,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,We should form teams to hunt \Nfor food, build houses,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.61,0:09:53.58,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,and strengthen the village defenses.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.80,0:09:55.36,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,We'll start with...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.13,0:09:58.81,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,What was his name again?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.81,0:10:00.96,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, do they even have names?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.57,0:10:03.85,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, what are all of your names, anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.85,0:10:07.09,Main,Elder,0000,0000,0000,,We monsters do not normally have names.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.09,0:10:10.97,Main,Elder,0000,0000,0000,,Even without names, we can still \Ncommunicate our thoughts to one another.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.97,0:10:12.46,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, really?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.60,0:10:16.10,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,But it's more convenient to have names,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.10,0:10:18.88,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,so I'd like to name you all. Is that okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.17,0:10:22.07,Main,Elder,0000,0000,0000,,N-Name us?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.07,0:10:24.29,Main,Elder,0000,0000,0000,,A-Are you certain?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.29,0:10:25.67,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,S-Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.62,0:10:33.95,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Why are they so excited over something \Nas simple as getting a name?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.38,0:10:39.94,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, we'll start with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.34,0:10:42.48,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Hmm, let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.86,0:10:46.00,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,What did you call the son \Nyou had who died in battle?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.68,0:10:48.18,Main,Elder,0000,0000,0000,,Rigur.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.18,0:10:49.66,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Rigur, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.05,0:10:52.02,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Then you'll be Rigurd.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.02,0:10:53.12,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Rigurd!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.01,0:10:57.39,Main,Rigurd,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you so much! Rigurd! I am so moved!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.63,0:10:59.24,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,R-Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.74,0:11:02.10,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,I just picked it because \Nit had the same sound...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.76,0:11:05.18,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,You'll inherit your brother's name: Rigur.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.60,0:11:06.54,Main,Rigur,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.54,0:11:11.11,Main,Rigurd,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so grateful that my son has been \Nallowed to inherit Rigur's name!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.63,0:11:14.03,Main,Both,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you so much!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.52,0:11:17.57,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Where the heck are these \Nreactions coming from?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.44,0:11:22.73,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,You're Gobta.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.73,0:11:25.20,Main,Gobta,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes, sir! Thank you, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.72,0:11:27.17,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,You're Gobchi.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.04,0:11:29.00,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Gobtsu.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.48,0:11:30.51,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Gobte.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.30,0:11:32.78,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,And you're Gobzo.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.64,0:11:35.82,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,These names are getting \Nmore and more careless...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.82,0:11:38.38,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,I feel bad seeing them so happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.38,0:11:43.44,Main,Rigurd,0000,0000,0000,,Um... We truly do appreciate \Nyou giving us all names, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.30,0:11:47.89,Main,Rigurd,0000,0000,0000,,We are aware that your \Nmagical power is immense,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.89,0:11:52.47,Main,Rigurd,0000,0000,0000,,but are you sure it's all right \Nto give all of us names at once?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.05,0:11:54.72,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I don't see any problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.72,0:11:57.03,Main,Rigurd,0000,0000,0000,,Well, if you are certain...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.03,0:11:58.12,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Who's next?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.52,0:12:01.93,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,You'll be... Haruna!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.93,0:12:02.79,Main,Haruna,0000,0000,0000,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.81,0:12:09.35,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,That takes care of all the Goblins.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.35,0:12:10.76,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Next is...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.76,0:12:15.56,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,He's the son of the Direwolf boss, isn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.56,0:12:18.22,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder if he holds a grudge against me...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.22,0:12:19.31,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Actually...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.70,0:12:23.31,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,They don't seem to be \Nholding any grudges at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.64,0:12:25.61,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Hmm...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.61,0:12:27.81,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Wolf, fangs...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.36,0:12:32.86,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Wind... Storm...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.28,0:12:36.13,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,I know. I'll give him my family name.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.54,0:12:37.89,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Tempest...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.89,0:12:39.58,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Tempest Fang...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.58,0:12:41.33,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Storm Fang...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.33,0:12:42.87,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Ranga...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.87,0:12:45.33,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! Ranga! I like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.22,0:12:48.45,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,All right! Your name is Ranga!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.67,0:12:50.55,Skill,Text,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(320,240)\fad(524,1)}— (Storm)   (Fang) —
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.31,0:12:50.32,Main,Ranga,0000,0000,0000,,Ranga...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.40,0:12:53.57,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,I think he likes it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.80,0:12:57.09,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What's going on? My body...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.09,0:12:57.99,Main,Ranga,0000,0000,0000,,Rimuru-sama?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.99,0:12:59.81,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Everything... is getting... dark...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.81,0:13:00.88,Main,Goblin,0000,0000,0000,,Rimuru-sama!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.88,0:13:02.58,Main,Goblin,0000,0000,0000,,Please stay strong!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.81,0:13:03.65,Italics_Top,Great Sage,0000,0000,0000,,Warning.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.85,0:13:03.52,sign_18770_195_Warning,Text,0000,0000,0000,,Warning
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.56,0:13:06.14,sign_18787_197_Magicule_reserve,Text,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(483,1680)}Magicule reserves below minimum limit
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.65,0:13:06.60,Italics_Top,Great Sage,0000,0000,0000,,Internal magicule reserves have \Nfallen below the minimum limit.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.95,0:13:09.10,Italics_Top,Great Sage,0000,0000,0000,,Entering sleep mode.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.10,0:13:12.19,Italics_Top,Great Sage,0000,0000,0000,,Estimated time to full recovery: three days.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.70,0:13:14.81,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,I used up too many magicules?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.81,0:13:16.32,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,How...?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.59,0:13:25.09,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't move, speak, \Nor sense my surroundings,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.09,0:13:26.58,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,but I was conscious.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.06,0:13:37.09,Main,Rigurd,0000,0000,0000,,It must have been because he \Nnamed so many of us at once...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.00,0:13:42.85,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently, giving names to \Nmonsters uses up magicules.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.85,0:13:45.77,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,I guess that's why Rigurd was so worried.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.77,0:13:47.60,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Is that common knowledge among monsters?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.98,0:13:50.32,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,You should've said so!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.27,0:13:59.82,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Then, three days later...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.41,0:14:09.04,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Full recovery!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.60,0:14:11.14,Main,Haruna,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Rimuru-sama!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.14,0:14:12.71,Main,Haruna,0000,0000,0000,,Good morning!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.96,0:14:14.52,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.52,0:14:16.83,Main,Haruna,0000,0000,0000,,You seem to be all better.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.50,0:14:18.63,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Who's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.63,0:14:21.47,Main,Haruna,0000,0000,0000,,I'll go get Elder Rigurd.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.47,0:14:22.72,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.50,0:14:27.10,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Did this village have a girl that cute in it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.10,0:14:30.09,Main,Rigurd,0000,0000,0000,,Rimuru-sama! Have you awakened?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.09,0:14:31.40,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Rigurd!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.61,0:14:35.33,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,That woman who... was... just...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.33,0:14:36.65,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.87,0:14:39.11,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,I am Rigurd.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.46,0:14:41.93,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,What happened in the last three days?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.93,0:14:44.17,Main,Rigurd,0000,0000,0000,,It's because you gave us names!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.17,0:14:45.54,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Just from that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.54,0:14:48.01,Main,Rigurd,0000,0000,0000,,Becoming a monster with a name
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.01,0:14:52.83,Main,Rigurd,0000,0000,0000,,raises one's rank as a monster \Nand causes one to evolve!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.37,0:14:54.54,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,I-I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.94,0:14:58.87,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,So that's why you were all so \Nhappy just to be getting names.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.27,0:15:02.13,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,No wonder that sucked my magicules dry...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.60,0:15:10.14,Main,Ranga,0000,0000,0000,,Master, allow me to express my \Nutmost joy at your recovery!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.38,0:15:13.11,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,That horn... The star on your forehead...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.11,0:15:14.59,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,You're Ranga, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.59,0:15:15.38,Main,Ranga,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.31,0:15:23.66,Main,Goblins,0000,0000,0000,,Rimuru-sama!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.90,0:15:34.53,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,There's Rigurd...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.87,0:15:36.95,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,And Rigur...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.29,0:15:39.60,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,And Gobta...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.59,0:15:42.63,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Well, you didn't change much.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.37,0:15:45.78,Main,Goblins,0000,0000,0000,,Rimuru-sama! Rimuru-sama!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.36,0:15:48.52,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,It's not so much like they evolved.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.52,0:15:51.10,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,They're like totally different monsters.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.10,0:15:53.40,Italics_Top,Great Sage,0000,0000,0000,,The male Goblins have evolved to Hobgoblins,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.40,0:15:56.15,Italics_Top,Great Sage,0000,0000,0000,,and the females to Goblinas.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.83,0:16:11.04,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Ranga, if I recall, you were \Nthe only Direwolf I named...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.65,0:16:14.54,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,so why did all of the Direwolves evolve?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.40,0:16:20.64,Main,Ranga,0000,0000,0000,,Master, all of us Direwolves are as one.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.64,0:16:23.59,Main,Ranga,0000,0000,0000,,Our brethren are all connected.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.59,0:16:26.80,Main,Ranga,0000,0000,0000,,Therefore, my name has \Nbecome our clan's name.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.56,0:16:32.31,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Huh... So your entire clan \Nevolved through a shared name?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.52,0:16:35.78,Main,Ranga,0000,0000,0000,,We are no longer the Direwolves.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.38,0:16:38.05,Main,Ranga,0000,0000,0000,,We are the Tempest Wolves!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.38,0:16:41.25,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Tempest Wolves...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.25,0:16:42.90,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Well, good for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.46,0:16:50.20,Main,Ranga,0000,0000,0000,,Master!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.51,0:16:53.28,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Can't you show a little consideration?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.66,0:16:54.95,Main,Ranga,0000,0000,0000,,I-I'm so sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.09,0:16:59.29,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,You can change your own size?! That's handy!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.85,0:17:02.72,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Well, the evolving isn't so bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.72,0:17:05.66,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,The problem is what to \Ndo about food, shelter,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.66,0:17:08.30,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,and clothing to sustain both \Nthe Goblins and the Wolves...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.61,0:17:14.81,Main,Ranga,0000,0000,0000,,Master!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.31,0:17:33.50,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Right, it took five minutes \Nfor all of you to quiet down.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.83,0:17:38.08,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,They didn't get my best joke?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.76,0:17:41.27,Main,Rigurd,0000,0000,0000,,Rimuru-sama, what did you mean by that?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.21,0:17:43.83,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,F-Forget about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.26,0:17:48.08,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,As you can see, we're a huge family now.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.49,0:17:52.02,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,So to avoid problems, I think \Nwe should set some rules.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.02,0:17:53.72,Main,All,0000,0000,0000,,Rules?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.01,0:17:55.56,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,There are three rules.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.56,0:17:58.10,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like you to uphold \Nthem, at the very least.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.10,0:18:00.48,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,First, no attacking humans.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.96,0:18:03.48,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Second, no fighting amongst yourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.17,0:18:06.49,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Third, no belittling other races.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.00,0:18:07.91,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,That's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.71,0:18:11.22,Main,Riguru,0000,0000,0000,,Sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.22,0:18:12.24,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, Rigur-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.01,0:18:15.75,Main,Rigur,0000,0000,0000,,Why aren't we allowed to attack humans?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.75,0:18:17.34,Main,Rigurd,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hey! Rigur!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.34,0:18:19.25,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,It's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.83,0:18:21.47,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,The reason is simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.47,0:18:24.50,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,It's because I like humans. That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.66,0:18:27.26,Main,Rigur,0000,0000,0000,,I see! Now I understand!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.45,0:18:29.85,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? You... understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.85,0:18:30.82,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.04,0:18:36.71,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Um, so, listen... Humans live in groups.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.71,0:18:39.39,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,If you mess with them, \Nthey could retaliate in a big way.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.17,0:18:43.41,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,And if they came after us in earnest, \NI doubt we could handle them.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.41,0:18:46.98,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, getting along benefits \Nus in lots of ways, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.06,0:18:50.91,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Any other questions?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.09,0:18:51.72,Main,Gobta,0000,0000,0000,,Me!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.72,0:18:52.72,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Gobta-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.21,0:18:56.29,Main,Gobta,0000,0000,0000,,What did you mean by \N"no belittling other races"?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.00,0:18:59.88,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Well, you've all gotten \Nstronger by evolving, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.88,0:19:03.54,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,It means you shouldn't let that get to \Nyour head and push weaker races around.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.01,0:19:06.26,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Don't make the mistake of thinking \Nyou're better than them.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.26,0:19:10.19,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,You don't want them getting stronger \Nthemselves and retaliating someday, do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.19,0:19:11.77,Main,Gobta,0000,0000,0000,,Got it, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.26,0:19:16.10,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,That's about it. Do your \Nbest to follow those rules.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.10,0:19:17.09,Main,All,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.52,0:19:19.31,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Also...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.90,0:19:23.93,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Elder Rigurd, I declare you the Goblin Lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.29,0:19:25.61,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,The lord of the Goblins!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.24,0:19:27.54,Italics,Rigurd,0000,0000,0000,,Lord?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.15,0:19:30.57,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Lead your village well.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.26,0:19:34.61,Main,Rigurd,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.61,0:19:39.81,Main,Rigurd,0000,0000,0000,,I, Rigurd, accept this \Nresponsibility on pain of death!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.81,0:19:41.33,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Good. I'm counting on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.42,0:19:46.71,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Frankly, I was just dumping the job on \Nhim. I didn't expect him to be so moved.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.55,0:19:53.69,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,I then gave jobs to all the Goblins.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.11,0:19:56.22,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,I assigned a team to keep watch \Non the surrounding area...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.55,0:20:00.45,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,and a team to gather food.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.95,0:20:03.72,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't look like there'll \Nbe any problems with these two.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.81,0:20:06.90,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,The problem is...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.30,0:20:10.39,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,The team that builds houses, and \Nthe team that makes clothes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.39,0:20:13.18,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,The "shelter and clothing" part \Nof "food, shelter, and clothing."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.61,0:20:15.35,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,I wouldn't call that a house.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.05,0:20:19.54,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,I can't do any more than \Nbasic handyman stuff,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.54,0:20:22.66,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,but I worked in general contracting, \Nso I know good from bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.66,0:20:24.26,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,And this...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.65,0:20:29.42,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,You don't need to be a general \Ncontractor to figure it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.39,0:20:32.03,Main,Rigurd,0000,0000,0000,,This is most embarrassing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.03,0:20:33.49,Main,Rigur,0000,0000,0000,,Forgive us.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.17,0:20:35.93,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,And as for your clothes...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.67,0:20:43.22,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,I-I think they're a little too revealing!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.19,0:20:47.15,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,That's not necessarily a bad thing, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.93,0:20:50.13,Main,Rigur,0000,0000,0000,,There is no one here with \Nthe skill to make them.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.13,0:20:50.94,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.13,0:20:54.12,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,I-If you can't make them, \Ncouldn't you get some from somewhere?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.93,0:20:58.61,Main,Rigurd,0000,0000,0000,,There are some with whom we have \Nattempted to trade a few times.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.02,0:21:02.21,Main,Rigurd,0000,0000,0000,,Aside from clothing, \Nthey are also quite skilled,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.21,0:21:04.56,Main,Rigurd,0000,0000,0000,,so they may know how to build houses, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.56,0:21:05.45,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Hmm...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.45,0:21:07.34,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Well, we're getting nowhere this way,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.34,0:21:09.24,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,so maybe we should go see them.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.24,0:21:10.58,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Who, and where, are they?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.03,0:21:13.84,Main,Rigurd,0000,0000,0000,,They are the Dwarves, \Nand they live in Dwargon.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.19,0:21:15.37,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Dwarves!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.37,0:21:17.84,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,You mean the famous \Nmasters of metalworking?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.49,0:21:20.60,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Now I have no choice but to go!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.60,0:21:23.96,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,I'll try going to Dwargon.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.96,0:21:26.60,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Rigurd, can you look after \Nthe village while I'm away?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.76,0:21:27.52,Main,Rigurd,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.52,0:21:31.09,Main,Rigurd,0000,0000,0000,,Leave everything to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.52,0:21:40.49,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,All right, I'll see you later!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.49,0:21:41.96,Main,Goblins,0000,0000,0000,,Goodbye!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.96,0:21:43.58,Main,Rigurd,0000,0000,0000,,Safe travels!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.58,0:21:45.50,Main,Haruna,0000,0000,0000,,Come back soon!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.14,0:21:53.17,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,And so I left the village \Nto go and meet the Dwarves.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.56,0:21:57.58,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,I'm told this Dwargon place \Nis a pretty big city,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.58,0:21:59.32,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,and it even has a king.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.63,0:22:04.19,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a little... no, I'm really excited!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.95,0:23:38.90,Italics_Top,Great Sage,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, "In the Kingdom of the Dwarves."
